The paper discusses the use of computational intelligence techniques in wireless sensor networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on distributed optimization and network features, which could also place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The use of optimization algorithms and analysis of network parameters could also suggest a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves testing and profiling of the system, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
